  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Gill's Exposition of the Entire Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "And David said to all the congregation,.... Consisting of princes, captains, and officers, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Chronicles 28:1",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "now bless the Lord your God; as he had done, for putting it into the power of their hands, and into their hearts, to do what they had: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and all the congregation blessed the Lord God of their fathers; some one as the mouth of the rest put up a thanksgiving to God, as David directed, to which they all assented, and in which they all joined: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and bowed down their heads, and worshipped the Lord and the king; the one with religious worship, the other with civil; the Syriac and Arabic versions more plainly distinguish, \"they worshipped the Lord, and blessed David the king\"; though some think Solomon, now made king, is meant. ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "and bowed down their heads, and worshipped the Lord and the king; the one with religious worship, the other with civil; the Syriac and Arabic versions more plainly distinguish, \"they worshipped the Lord, and blessed David the king\"; though some think Solomon, now made king, is meant. ",
            "children": []
